<paragraph id="625836AFE24EFF87FE22FDD8FED1FD5C" blockId="8.[264,1323,431,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<materialsCitation id="D28F3CF2E24EFF87FE22FDD8FED5FD5C" collectionCode="T" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" specimenCode="T1, T4" specimenCount="2" specimenCount-female="1" specimenCount-male="1">
Differential diagnosis. 
<specimenCount id="74E1FD26E24EFF87FD59FDD9FDE8FD37" box="[579,599,630,650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="74E1FD26E24EFF87FD95FDD7FD1EFD37" box="[655,673,632,650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Body mainly black. Head about as long as wide. Terga without apical hair bands. Marginal zone of 
<specimenCode id="32419ED4E24EFF87FC34FD30FCF3FD04" box="[814,844,671,697]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T1</specimenCode>
­ 
<specimenCode id="32419ED4E24EFF87FC4FFD30FCC6FD04" box="[853,889,671,697]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T4</specimenCode>
with few appressed hair on lateral margins
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="625836AFE24EFF87FE22FD40FD35FC6C" blockId="8.[264,1323,431,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Diagnosis (
<figureCitation id="FADC2A2AE24EFF87FEA7FD40FDB8FCB4" box="[445,519,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[264,367,1610,1634]" captionTargetBox="[305,1292,1109,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-213@8.[299,1296,1105,1595]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Eremaphanta iranica, male (scale=300µm); a. Sternum 7; b. Sternum 8; c. Dorsal view of genitalia; from Schwammberger (1971)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5058063/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<specimenCount id="74E1FD26E24EFF87FD07FD41FD8EFCBF" box="[541,561,750,770]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. Unknown. 
<specimenCount id="74E1FD26E24EFF87FDD8FD5FFD6CFCBF" box="[706,723,752,770]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Tb1­Tb3 and tarsi yellow; other parts of the body entirely black. Head nearly as long as wide. Antennae dorsally brownish, ventrally yellowish. Propodeal triangle dull and rugose. Disc of terga with short brown appressed hairs. Marginal zone of 
<collectionCode id="04F6AE6AE24EFF87FD34FCC8FDFDFC3C" box="[558,578,871,897]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T</collectionCode>
1­ 
<collectionCode id="04F6AE6AE24EFF87FD4FFCC8FDD6FC3C" box="[597,617,871,897]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T</collectionCode>
4 with few appressed hair on lateral margins. Premarginal line of S1­S5 slightly emarginate or straight. S7­S8 and genitalia as figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="06764B5EE24EFF87FE12FC18FD9BFC6C" author="Schwammberger, K. - H." box="[264,548,951,977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10170" refString="Schwammberger, K. - H. (1971) Zwei neue Bienen-Arten aus dem Iran (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Stuttgarter Beitrge zur Naturkunde, 225, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1971">Schwammberger (1971)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation id="FADC2A2AE24EFF87FD2EFC18FDC2FC6C" box="[564,637,951,977]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[264,367,1610,1634]" captionTargetBox="[305,1292,1109,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-213@8.[299,1296,1105,1595]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Eremaphanta iranica, male (scale=300µm); a. Sternum 7; b. Sternum 8; c. Dorsal view of genitalia; from Schwammberger (1971)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5058063/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="625836AFE24EFF87FE22FC70FCB7FC44" blockId="8.[264,1323,431,1057]" box="[312,776,991,1017]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
